      • registerRestartable

        public void registerRestartable(int restartableId,
                       rx.functions.Func0<rx.Subscription> factory)
        A restartable is any RxJava query/request that can be started (subscribed) and should be automatically restarted (re-subscribed) after a process restart.

        Registers a factory for a restartable. Re-subscribes the restartable after a process restart.

        Parameters:
        restartableId - id of a restartable.
        factory - a factory that will create an actual rxjava subscription when requested.

      • subscribeRestartable

        public void subscribeRestartable(int restartableId)
        Subscribes (runs) a restartable using a factory method provided with registerRestartable(int, rx.functions.Func0<rx.Subscription>). If a presenter gets lost during a process restart while a restartable is still subscribed, the restartable will be restarted on next registerRestartable(int, rx.functions.Func0<rx.Subscription>) call.

        If the restartable is already subscribed then it will be unsubscribed first.

        Parameters:
        restartableId - id of a restartable.

      • deliver

        public <T> rx.Observable.Transformer<T,T> deliver()
        Returns a transformer that will delay onNext, onError and onComplete emissions unless a view become available. getView() is guaranteed to be != null during all emissions. This transformer can only be used on application's main thread.

        Use this operator if you need to deliver *all* emissions to a view, in example when you're sending items into adapter one by one.

        Type Parameters:
        T - a type of onNext value.
        Returns:
        the delaying operator.

      • deliverLatest

        public <T> rx.Observable.Transformer<T,T> deliverLatest()
        Returns a transformer that will delay onNext, onError and onComplete emissions unless a view become available. getView() is guaranteed to be != null during all emissions. This transformer can only be used on application's main thread.

        If this transformer receives a next value while the previous value has not been delivered, the previous value will be dropped.

        Use this operator when you need to show updatable data.

        Type Parameters:
        T - a type of onNext value.
        Returns:
        the delaying operator.

      • deliverLatestCache

        public <T> rx.Observable.Transformer<T,T> deliverLatestCache()
        Returns a transformer that will delay onNext, onError and onComplete emissions unless a view become available. getView() is guaranteed to be != null during all emissions. This transformer can only be used on application's main thread.

        If the transformer receives a next value while the previous value has not been delivered, the previous value will be dropped.

        The transformer will duplicate the latest onNext emission in case if a view has been reattached.

        This operator ignores onComplete emission and never sends one.

        Use this operator when you need to show updatable data that needs to be cached in memory.

        Type Parameters:
        T - a type of onNext value.
        Returns:
        the delaying operator.
